1
00:00:01,041 --> 00:00:02,601
BILL: What happened to the Doctor?

2
00:00:02,681 --> 00:00:04,041
The Doctor took you to safety.

3
00:00:04,121 --> 00:00:05,161
He paid a price.

4
00:00:05,241 --> 00:00:06,281
You're blind.

5
00:00:06,361 --> 00:00:07,361
It's temporary.

6
00:00:07,441 --> 00:00:10,761
-Look at me!
-Nardole, I can't. I really can't.

7
00:00:12,041 --> 00:00:14,921
I can't look at anything ever again.

8
00:00:16,121 --> 00:00:18,081
I'm still blind.

9
00:00:19,761 --> 00:00:23,041
MAN: Death is an increasing problem.

10
00:00:24,881 --> 00:00:29,801
With over a billion intelligent species
active in this galaxy alone,

11
00:00:29,881 --> 00:00:34,761
it is an ever greater challenge to know
how to kill all of them.

12
00:00:35,481 --> 00:00:38,601
On this planet, we are proud to serve
as executioners

13
00:00:38,681 --> 00:00:41,601
to every living thing.

14
00:00:42,201 --> 00:00:47,201
The destruction of a Time Lord,
however, is a particular honour.

15
00:00:48,601 --> 00:00:50,761
This technology is precisely calibrated.

16
00:00:51,561 --> 00:00:52,721
As you can see,

17
00:00:54,081 --> 00:00:58,281
it will stop both hearts,
all three brain stems,

18
00:00:58,401 --> 00:01:00,361
and deliver a cellular shockwave

19
00:01:00,441 --> 00:01:03,761
that will permanently disable
regenerative ability.

20
00:01:05,321 --> 00:01:06,601
I know how it works.

21
00:01:07,041 --> 00:01:08,881
You certainly will in a moment.

22
00:01:11,201 --> 00:01:12,641
Following termination,

23
00:01:13,321 --> 00:01:15,561
the body will be placed
in a quantum fold chamber

24
00:01:15,641 --> 00:01:18,561
under constant guard
for no less than a thousand years.

25
00:01:19,201 --> 00:01:22,961
In case of, shall we say, relapses.

26
00:01:24,241 --> 00:01:27,121
Life can be a cunning enemy.

27
00:01:27,641 --> 00:01:30,841
An additional stipulation
of the fatality index

28
00:01:32,561 --> 00:01:35,281
is that the sentence must be carried out
by another Time Lord.

29
00:01:36,561 --> 00:01:39,721
Apologies for our choice,
but your people are not easy to come by.

30
00:01:43,121 --> 00:01:45,281
Oh, Doctor?

31
00:01:45,641 --> 00:01:47,601
I didn't expect you.

32
00:01:48,121 --> 00:01:49,881
Thought you'd retired.

33
00:01:50,001 --> 00:01:52,681
Domestic bliss on Darillium.

34
00:01:53,041 --> 00:01:54,961
That's the word among the Daleks.

35
00:01:55,681 --> 00:01:56,961
What happened?

36
00:01:59,321 --> 00:02:00,441
Oh, I see.

37
00:02:02,601 --> 00:02:03,721
My condolences.

38
00:02:13,681 --> 00:02:15,961
The prisoner will kneel.

39
00:02:25,041 --> 00:02:26,201
Right.

40
00:02:29,121 --> 00:02:30,241
Thank you.

41
00:02:40,841 --> 00:02:43,121
They can't know I'm blind, Missy.

42
00:02:43,201 --> 00:02:44,401
No one can know.

43
00:02:44,721 --> 00:02:47,121
Memories are so much worse in the dark.

44
00:02:55,841 --> 00:02:58,081
The quantum fold chamber is prepared.

45
00:02:58,161 --> 00:02:59,241
Great.

46
00:02:59,961 --> 00:03:02,121
The sentence will be carried out.

47
00:03:05,441 --> 00:03:06,441
Executioner?

48
00:03:16,601 --> 00:03:18,841
Please, I'll do anything.

49
00:03:22,401 --> 00:03:23,641
Just let me live.

50
00:03:26,001 --> 00:03:27,481
(DEVICE TRILLS)

51
00:03:40,041 --> 00:03:42,081
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

52
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:23,841
(DOOR OPENS)

53
00:04:27,641 --> 00:04:28,681
Hello?

54
00:04:32,121 --> 00:04:34,121
Hello? Who's there?

55
00:04:34,201 --> 00:04:36,241
CARDINAL ANGELO: Good evening, Doctor.

56
00:04:39,961 --> 00:04:43,241
We have come here today,
direct from the Vatican.

57
00:04:43,321 --> 00:04:45,241
All right, that's nice.

58
00:04:45,441 --> 00:04:47,321
Well, if you've got a collecting tin,

59
00:04:47,681 --> 00:04:49,081
I'm sure I can find something.

60
00:04:49,161 --> 00:04:50,481
Uh, leaky roof, is it?

61
00:04:50,721 --> 00:04:52,561
Oh, no. (CHUCKLING)

62
00:04:52,641 --> 00:04:55,281
No. No, no. No, no, no. Stop talking.

63
00:04:55,681 --> 00:04:59,641
Stop now. Please, just listen to them.
Sounds important.

64
00:04:59,761 --> 00:05:01,361
We have come here to see you,

65
00:05:01,441 --> 00:05:05,761
because your services of wisdom
are recommended at the highest level.

66
00:05:12,721 --> 00:05:13,841
As you can see,

67
00:05:13,921 --> 00:05:16,681
this is a personal recommendation
of Pope Benedict IX...

68
00:05:17,921 --> 00:05:19,281
...in 1045,

69
00:05:19,361 --> 00:05:20,601
(CHUCKLES)

70
00:05:21,601 --> 00:05:22,801
Pope Benedict.

71
00:05:23,041 --> 00:05:24,481
Lovely girl. What a night.

72
00:05:25,001 --> 00:05:27,001
I knew she was trouble,

73
00:05:27,081 --> 00:05:28,841
but she wove a spell
with her castanets.

74
00:05:28,921 --> 00:05:32,961
Doctor, on behalf of every human soul
in this world,

75
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:34,441
of any creed, of any faith,

76
00:05:35,081 --> 00:05:36,801
with the utmost respect

77
00:05:37,041 --> 00:05:38,361
and in complete secrecy,

78
00:05:38,441 --> 00:05:41,281
His Holiness, the Pope,
the Bishop of Rome,

79
00:05:41,361 --> 00:05:44,721
request most urgently
a personal audience.

80
00:05:45,601 --> 00:05:48,241
Well, if he was so keen to talk to me,
why didn't he just come here himself?

81
00:05:48,361 --> 00:05:51,281
He is here.
He's standing right in front of us.

82
00:05:52,521 --> 00:05:53,721
Hello.

83
00:05:54,321 --> 00:05:57,881
Uh, the Pope. I'm sorry
that I didn't recognise you there.

84
00:06:00,121 --> 00:06:01,761
You don't do this.

85
00:06:02,681 --> 00:06:07,161
The Pope doesn't zoom around the world
in the Popemobile surprising people.

86
00:06:08,441 --> 00:06:09,801
Why would you do that?

87
00:06:09,921 --> 00:06:12,001
-(SPEAKING ITALIAN)
-Mmm-hmm.

88
00:06:13,401 --> 00:06:14,481
Extremis.

89
00:06:19,001 --> 00:06:20,761
CARDINAL ANGELO:
There is an ancient text

90
00:06:21,281 --> 00:06:24,121
buried deep in the most secret
of the Vatican libraries.

91
00:06:24,361 --> 00:06:26,521
Text older than the church itself.

92
00:06:31,281 --> 00:06:35,361
The language of this text is lost to us.

93
00:06:35,841 --> 00:06:39,121
But thanks to the work
of an early Christian sect,

94
00:06:39,481 --> 00:06:42,441
the title has survived.

95
00:06:43,961 --> 00:06:45,401
Okay, so, what's the title?

96
00:06:46,761 --> 00:06:51,721
Oh, yes, I can see
that it says, uh, "Veritas”.

97
00:06:51,801 --> 00:06:53,841
Oh. Hmm.

98
00:06:54,201 --> 00:06:56,081
Literally, "the Truth”.

99
00:06:56,921 --> 00:06:59,881
Obviously, this sect,
they understood the language.

100
00:06:59,961 --> 00:07:01,041
CARDINAL ANGELO: It died with them.

101
00:07:01,121 --> 00:07:03,201
And all copies of their translation

102
00:07:03,281 --> 00:07:06,201
disappeared shortly
after their mass suicide.

103
00:07:06,801 --> 00:07:10,081
Few months ago,
after many centuries of work,

104
00:07:10,921 --> 00:07:13,641
the Veritas was translated again.

105
00:07:14,761 --> 00:07:17,161
Right. And?

106
00:07:17,401 --> 00:07:18,801
DOCTOR: What did it say?

107
00:07:19,321 --> 00:07:20,321
No one knows.

108
00:07:20,801 --> 00:07:24,601
Everyone who worked on the translation
and everyone who subsequently read it

109
00:07:24,681 --> 00:07:25,801
is now dead.

110
00:07:28,841 --> 00:07:31,961
Dead, Doctor, by their own hand.

111
00:07:33,281 --> 00:07:35,361
The Veritasis a short document.

112
00:07:35,521 --> 00:07:36,841
A few pages only.

113
00:07:37,001 --> 00:07:39,881
And yet contains a secret

114
00:07:40,161 --> 00:07:43,401
that drives all who know it
to destroy themselves.

115
00:07:43,601 --> 00:07:45,001
Confirmed suicides, all of them?

116
00:07:45,081 --> 00:07:46,841
In every case, beyond doubt.

117
00:07:46,921 --> 00:07:48,081
DOCTOR: All bodies recovered?

118
00:07:48,561 --> 00:07:51,121
Except one. But we naturally assumed...

119
00:07:51,201 --> 00:07:52,561
DOCTOR: Assume nothing.

120
00:07:52,641 --> 00:07:54,761
Assumption makes an
ass out of you and umption.

121
00:07:54,841 --> 00:07:56,881
Cardinal, one of your
translators is missing.

122
00:07:56,961 --> 00:08:00,921
Doctor, those translators
were devout believers.

123
00:08:01,001 --> 00:08:02,721
They took their own lives

124
00:08:02,961 --> 00:08:05,961
in the knowledge that suicide
is a mortal sin.

125
00:08:06,481 --> 00:08:09,841
They read the Veritas and chose hell.

126
00:08:10,521 --> 00:08:11,681
Dottore...

127
00:08:13,601 --> 00:08:16,321
(IN ENGLISH) Will you read the Veritas?

128
00:08:23,281 --> 00:08:24,881
-Loo through there.
-Oh, ta.

129
00:08:24,961 --> 00:08:26,441
I thought you moved out from here.

130
00:08:26,681 --> 00:08:29,281
Yeah, slightly didn't work out.
(CHUCKLES)

131
00:08:29,361 --> 00:08:31,121
Second attempt on the way.

132
00:08:37,961 --> 00:08:39,161
Did I hear voices?

133
00:08:39,561 --> 00:08:41,641
I thought you were going out
with Harry tonight.

134
00:08:41,841 --> 00:08:43,721
-Howard.
-I don't like knowing the names,

135
00:08:43,841 --> 00:08:44,881
I only get attached.

136
00:08:45,441 --> 00:08:46,961
Did you bring someone home?

137
00:08:47,921 --> 00:08:49,121
(HESITANTLY) Yeah.

138
00:08:50,161 --> 00:08:52,281
I'm a grownup, I can do that, can't I?

139
00:08:52,401 --> 00:08:55,281
Of course not. I have very strict rules
about men.

140
00:08:55,521 --> 00:08:57,241
Probably not as strict as mine.

141
00:08:58,001 --> 00:08:59,201
(TOILET FLUSHING)

142
00:09:01,161 --> 00:09:02,201
(DOOR SHUTS)

143
00:09:02,921 --> 00:09:04,121
Oh, hello, are you Moira?

144
00:09:04,201 --> 00:09:06,241
-(MOUTHING)
-Oh, you're a girl.

145
00:09:06,321 --> 00:09:07,441
Mmm. I'm Penny.

146
00:09:07,521 --> 00:09:08,841
Oh. Oh. (CHUCKLES)

147
00:09:08,921 --> 00:09:10,721
Oh, I see. Oh, I'm sorry.

148
00:09:10,801 --> 00:09:14,561
Here's me thinking she dragged
some poor terrified man home.

149
00:09:14,881 --> 00:09:16,801
-(PENNY LAUGHS)
-Well, phew!

150
00:09:16,881 --> 00:09:18,441
-Oh, phew.
-(BILL CHUCKLES)

151
00:09:18,521 --> 00:09:21,121
Right, you two. I'm off to the pub.

152
00:09:21,201 --> 00:09:22,721
Don't do anything I wouldn't do.

153
00:09:25,521 --> 00:09:26,921
-(DOOR SHUTS)
-Well...

154
00:09:27,281 --> 00:09:28,921
Alone at last.

155
00:09:31,121 --> 00:09:32,361
(CHUCKLES)

156
00:09:33,201 --> 00:09:35,241
(WHOOSHING)

157
00:09:38,921 --> 00:09:40,601
Oh, God. What was that?

158
00:09:40,921 --> 00:09:41,961
The, uh...

159
00:09:42,361 --> 00:09:43,721
...pipes.

160
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:45,801
It's... It's the... The pipes

161
00:09:45,881 --> 00:09:47,281
in... In my bedroom.

162
00:09:47,401 --> 00:09:50,201
Be warned. Sometimes I shout at them.

163
00:09:50,561 --> 00:09:51,681
Wha...

164
00:09:53,401 --> 00:09:54,561
Are you okay?

165
00:09:54,841 --> 00:09:57,161
Yeah, sorry,
I'm just not quite used to...

166
00:09:57,281 --> 00:09:58,601
...all of this.

167
00:09:58,681 --> 00:10:02,521
Well, whatever this is,

168
00:10:03,481 --> 00:10:06,521
and actually, it's not anything yet,

169
00:10:07,841 --> 00:10:11,081
it is absolutely nothing
to feel guilty about.

170
00:10:12,561 --> 00:10:14,641
-Okay?
-Okay.

171
00:10:15,241 --> 00:10:16,641
(DOOR OPENS)

172
00:10:18,721 --> 00:10:20,721
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

173
00:10:32,641 --> 00:10:33,801
That was the Pope.

174
00:10:34,881 --> 00:10:36,881
Bill, that was the Pope.

175
00:10:39,121 --> 00:10:40,241
Yeah, yeah, give me a minute.

176
00:10:40,321 --> 00:10:45,161
I am about to have a truly awesome word
with someone.

177
00:10:52,401 --> 00:10:54,161
-Oh, my God.
-No, Penny, wait.

178
00:10:54,241 --> 00:10:55,601
(GASPS)

179
00:10:55,681 --> 00:10:58,161
-(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)
-(GROANS)

180
00:11:00,481 --> 00:11:02,161
You're all going to hell.

181
00:11:02,961 --> 00:11:04,401
-(DOOR SHUTS)
-Doctor.

182
00:11:04,481 --> 00:11:05,841
Here's a tip.

183
00:11:06,321 --> 00:11:07,521
When I'm on a date,

184
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:12,241
when that rare and special thing
happens in my real life,

185
00:11:12,481 --> 00:11:16,561
do not, do not under any circumstances

186
00:11:16,681 --> 00:11:19,321
put the Pope in my bedroom.

187
00:11:19,681 --> 00:11:21,761
Okay. Now I know.

188
00:11:22,201 --> 00:11:24,641
Air cleared. Nardole will explain
what's going on.

189
00:11:27,401 --> 00:11:29,361
Uh, Doctor?

190
00:11:29,641 --> 00:11:33,961
(CLEARS THROAT) It, uh...
I think it's pretty serious.

191
00:11:34,361 --> 00:11:36,481
-What's happened?
-Well... (STUTTERS)

192
00:11:38,761 --> 00:11:40,121
You know the Vatican?

193
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:43,201
-Yeah.
-The one in Rome.

194
00:11:43,441 --> 00:11:44,921
NARDOLE: That's in Italy.

195
00:11:45,001 --> 00:11:46,241
-BILL: Yeah.
-And what is that?

196
00:11:46,321 --> 00:11:48,481
NARDOLE: Where the Pope lives.
DOCTOR: It's a sort of, uh,

197
00:11:48,561 --> 00:11:49,881
a reading aid.

198
00:11:50,841 --> 00:11:52,241
It looks dangerous.

199
00:11:53,321 --> 00:11:54,761
Completely deadly.

200
00:11:54,841 --> 00:11:57,801
But, uh, you know,
swings and roundabouts...

201
00:11:58,201 --> 00:12:01,321
Pope Benedict said that you were more
in need of confession

202
00:12:01,401 --> 00:12:02,561
than any man breathing.

203
00:12:02,681 --> 00:12:04,601
But when the offer was made,

204
00:12:04,761 --> 00:12:06,561
you replied it would take too much time.

205
00:12:08,441 --> 00:12:12,161
On behalf of the Catholic Church,
the offer stands.

206
00:12:17,201 --> 00:12:20,561
You seem like a man with regret
on his mind.

207
00:12:22,201 --> 00:12:23,321
(CROW CAWS)

208
00:12:25,841 --> 00:12:27,481
Have you requested a priest?

209
00:12:28,201 --> 00:12:29,441
MISSY: Oh, I haven't.

210
00:12:32,281 --> 00:12:33,641
Apparently, I have.

211
00:12:33,921 --> 00:12:35,761
I shall seek consultation.

212
00:12:37,241 --> 00:12:39,281
-(WRISTWATCH TRILLING)
-(SIGHS)

213
00:12:43,201 --> 00:12:46,681
There are 412 precedents
in the fatality index.

214
00:12:48,241 --> 00:12:51,801
Divine intervention therefore
is permitted for a maximum

215
00:12:51,881 --> 00:12:53,521
of five minutes.

216
00:12:53,601 --> 00:12:54,721
Five minutes.

217
00:12:55,121 --> 00:12:57,081
The executioner may now discuss

218
00:12:57,161 --> 00:13:00,281
his immortal soul
and any peril there unto.

219
00:13:07,161 --> 00:13:08,801
MAN: Greetings, sinner.

220
00:13:08,881 --> 00:13:11,601
Only in darkness are we revealed.

221
00:13:11,681 --> 00:13:13,481
I never sent for you.

222
00:13:13,561 --> 00:13:17,841
MAN: Goodness is not goodness
that seeks advantage.

223
00:13:18,041 --> 00:13:20,961
Good is good in the final hour.

224
00:13:21,121 --> 00:13:25,321
In the deepest pit, without hope,
without witness.

225
00:13:25,601 --> 00:13:26,841
Without reward.

226
00:13:27,401 --> 00:13:30,521
Virtue is only virtue in extremis.

227
00:13:30,601 --> 00:13:32,921
This is what he believes.

228
00:13:33,201 --> 00:13:36,441
And this is the reason above all,
I love him.

229
00:13:37,281 --> 00:13:40,361
My husband. My madman in a box.

230
00:13:40,481 --> 00:13:41,721
My Doctor.

231
00:13:47,321 --> 00:13:48,681
Your missus wouldn't approve.

232
00:13:48,801 --> 00:13:50,081
How the hell did you get here?

233
00:13:50,161 --> 00:13:51,321
Followed you from Darillium

234
00:13:51,401 --> 00:13:54,401
on the explicit orders
of your late wife, River Song.

235
00:13:54,521 --> 00:13:57,921
Warning, I have full permission
to kick your arse.

236
00:14:13,401 --> 00:14:17,001
Okay. So, you're blind
and you don't want your enemies to know.

237
00:14:17,121 --> 00:14:19,881
I get it. But why does it have to be
a secret from Bill?

238
00:14:20,161 --> 00:14:22,121
Because I don't like being
worried about.

239
00:14:22,201 --> 00:14:24,601
Around me, people should be worried
about themselves.

240
00:14:24,681 --> 00:14:27,081
-Yeah, shall I tell you the real reason?
-No.

241
00:14:27,161 --> 00:14:30,161
Because the moment you tell Bill,
it becomes real.

242
00:14:30,241 --> 00:14:32,401
And then you might
actually have to deal with it.

243
00:14:32,481 --> 00:14:35,321
Good point. Well made.
Definitely not telling her now.

244
00:14:36,001 --> 00:14:37,121
You're an idiot.

245
00:14:38,321 --> 00:14:39,841
Everyone knows that.

246
00:14:45,121 --> 00:14:47,121
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

247
00:14:50,281 --> 00:14:52,001
(TRANSLATING)
Here you must go without me.

248
00:14:52,921 --> 00:14:55,001
Cardinal Angelo will conduct you
to the library.

249
00:14:55,081 --> 00:14:57,121
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

250
00:14:58,201 --> 00:15:00,281
CARDINAL ANGELO: (TRANSLATING)
May God light your path.

251
00:15:01,481 --> 00:15:03,441
Well, we could certainly give it a go.

252
00:15:11,121 --> 00:15:13,761
The entrance to the Hereticum.

253
00:15:14,161 --> 00:15:18,121
The library of forbidden
and heretical texts.

254
00:15:18,641 --> 00:15:22,241
First instituted by your old friend,
Pope Benedict,

255
00:15:24,041 --> 00:15:26,281
who still guards the door.

256
00:15:27,361 --> 00:15:28,681
NARDOLE: You old dog.

257
00:15:35,561 --> 00:15:36,601
(GASPS)

258
00:15:36,681 --> 00:15:37,761
(BATS SQUEAKING)

259
00:15:47,921 --> 00:15:51,961
CARDINAL ANGELO:
Very few know this place exists.

260
00:15:55,081 --> 00:15:56,841
The library of blasphemy.

261
00:15:56,921 --> 00:15:58,001
The Hereticum.

262
00:15:59,561 --> 00:16:00,801
Harry Potter.

263
00:16:00,881 --> 00:16:01,921
Language.

264
00:16:04,081 --> 00:16:07,041
Please stay close to me.

265
00:16:08,281 --> 00:16:12,481
The layout is designed
to confuse the uninitiated.

266
00:16:12,881 --> 00:16:14,161
Sort of like religion, really.

267
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:17,641
You happy in those shades?

268
00:16:18,281 --> 00:16:19,721
Not dark enough for ya?

269
00:16:19,801 --> 00:16:21,401
In darkness, we are revealed.

270
00:16:26,001 --> 00:16:29,961
Remember, sinner,
in darkness we are revealed.

271
00:16:30,881 --> 00:16:32,201
I regret, gentlemen,

272
00:16:33,561 --> 00:16:35,361
this consultation is over.

273
00:16:35,441 --> 00:16:36,921
I regret it, too.

274
00:16:37,041 --> 00:16:39,441
The sentence must now be carried out.

275
00:16:39,841 --> 00:16:41,921
Well, take a few more minutes
if you like.

276
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:46,041
Knock yourself out. Actually, do...
Do that. Knock yourself right out.

277
00:16:59,281 --> 00:17:01,081
I'll be good, I promise.

278
00:17:01,281 --> 00:17:03,361
(STUTTERING)
I'll turn. I'll turn good. Please.

279
00:17:04,161 --> 00:17:06,201
Teach me. Teach me how to be...

280
00:17:06,761 --> 00:17:08,001
(VOICE BREAKS) ...good.

281
00:17:09,881 --> 00:17:11,281
Without hope.

282
00:17:12,241 --> 00:17:13,441
Without witness.

283
00:17:15,601 --> 00:17:17,521
Without reward.

284
00:17:21,201 --> 00:17:22,841
Who was your date, then?

285
00:17:22,921 --> 00:17:25,881
Uh, Penny. Uh, it's a long story.

286
00:17:31,881 --> 00:17:33,881
CARDINAL ANGELO: The very centre
of the Hereticum.

287
00:17:34,521 --> 00:17:36,921
Home of the Veritas
for over a thousand years.

288
00:17:37,241 --> 00:17:39,361
Truth in the heart of heresy.

289
00:17:39,601 --> 00:17:42,561
CARDINAL ANGELO: And death
in the heart of truth.

290
00:17:43,321 --> 00:17:45,681
You'd be wizard at writing
Christmas crackers, you two.

291
00:17:47,961 --> 00:17:50,041
NARDOLE: Doctor.
BILL: What's that?

292
00:17:50,441 --> 00:17:51,961
I don't know.

293
00:17:53,241 --> 00:17:58,441
Oh, look, it's er, a mysterious light
shining round a corner

294
00:17:58,521 --> 00:18:00,641
approximately 10 feet away.

295
00:18:01,041 --> 00:18:02,121
CARDINAL ANGELO: Hello.

296
00:18:03,561 --> 00:18:04,561
Who's there?

297
00:18:06,721 --> 00:18:07,841
Doctor?

298
00:18:08,401 --> 00:18:09,841
This library is forbidden.

299
00:18:10,161 --> 00:18:11,561
-No, wait!
-Who are you?

300
00:18:13,841 --> 00:18:15,561
What are you doing here?

301
00:18:15,721 --> 00:18:16,761
Speak!

302
00:18:20,041 --> 00:18:21,561
Speak to me!

303
00:18:26,441 --> 00:18:27,841
What's through there?
What's through that door?

304
00:18:28,361 --> 00:18:30,601
There's no door there. It's a wall.

305
00:18:39,761 --> 00:18:42,441
Impossible. Quite impossible.

306
00:18:44,121 --> 00:18:45,961
Let's take a look at the Ver/tas.

307
00:18:46,121 --> 00:18:47,801
I have a feeling the answers
might be there.

308
00:18:48,321 --> 00:18:50,441
I have to check if there
is a breach in the wall.

309
00:18:51,321 --> 00:18:53,161
I'll unlock the cage in a moment.

310
00:18:54,121 --> 00:18:55,281
Sure.

311
00:19:13,081 --> 00:19:15,201
Oh, my God!

312
00:19:15,441 --> 00:19:16,641
What's wrong?

313
00:19:16,721 --> 00:19:17,961
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

314
00:19:20,881 --> 00:19:22,041
Oh, hang on.

315
00:19:25,161 --> 00:19:26,361
I think there's someone in there.

316
00:19:26,921 --> 00:19:29,041
Yeah, we are very slightly getting that.

317
00:19:29,761 --> 00:19:30,881
MAN: I'm sorry.

318
00:19:32,561 --> 00:19:33,641
I'm sorry.

319
00:19:36,641 --> 00:19:37,681
I sent it.

320
00:19:39,401 --> 00:19:40,521
Sent what?

321
00:19:41,201 --> 00:19:42,481
I sent it, yes.

322
00:19:42,961 --> 00:19:44,201
Sent what? Where?

323
00:19:47,121 --> 00:19:48,601
No, stop!

324
00:19:49,001 --> 00:19:50,121
You'll just get lost.

325
00:19:50,441 --> 00:19:53,201
Cardinal Angelo, someone just broke
into your book cage.

326
00:19:53,561 --> 00:19:54,641
(CRIES OUT)

327
00:19:54,921 --> 00:19:56,441
Priest, by the look of him.

328
00:19:56,961 --> 00:19:58,161
Shot out the lock.

329
00:19:58,761 --> 00:20:00,201
Oh, well, he hasn't got far.

330
00:20:03,441 --> 00:20:05,761
So much for your
forbidden library, Cardinal.

331
00:20:10,681 --> 00:20:11,721
Doctor, look at this.

332
00:20:12,401 --> 00:20:13,481
Must have been his.

333
00:20:14,241 --> 00:20:15,361
Laptop.

334
00:20:15,841 --> 00:20:16,921
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

335
00:20:18,441 --> 00:20:19,841
Hey, there's Wi-Fi down here.

336
00:20:20,841 --> 00:20:23,161
Of course there's Wi-Fi. It's a library.

337
00:20:23,961 --> 00:20:25,641
Reading chair with a safety belt.

338
00:20:26,001 --> 00:20:27,241
What's CERN?

339
00:20:27,321 --> 00:20:28,321
-CERN?
-BILL: Yeah.

340
00:20:28,481 --> 00:20:30,321
DOCTOR: The European Organisation
for Nuclear Research.

341
00:20:30,401 --> 00:20:33,481
The largest particle physics laboratory
on this planet. Why?

342
00:20:34,441 --> 00:20:37,161
Because four hours ago, someone,
that priest presumably,

343
00:20:37,241 --> 00:20:38,241
emailed them a copy

344
00:20:38,321 --> 00:20:40,801
of the Veritastranslation
from this computer.

345
00:20:40,961 --> 00:20:41,961
BILL: Remember what he said.

346
00:20:42,161 --> 00:20:43,161
He said, "I sent it."

347
00:20:44,721 --> 00:20:45,801
He sent the Veritas.

348
00:20:45,921 --> 00:20:48,201
-And CERN have just replied.
-What'd they say?

349
00:20:50,361 --> 00:20:51,401
"Pray for us."

350
00:20:51,521 --> 00:20:53,521
When do a bunch of scientists
ask for prayers?

351
00:20:53,721 --> 00:20:54,961
The same time anyone does.

352
00:20:55,841 --> 00:20:58,641
When they're very, very afraid.

353
00:20:59,521 --> 00:21:02,001
Particle physicists and priests.

354
00:21:02,841 --> 00:21:04,601
What could scare them both?

355
00:21:09,361 --> 00:21:11,921
He's been down here for a while,
that guy. Whoever he is.

356
00:21:12,081 --> 00:21:14,081
I'd guess the missing translator.

357
00:21:14,601 --> 00:21:16,481
-That's promising.
-"Promising"?

358
00:21:16,601 --> 00:21:19,041
Yeah. At least one person
read the Veritas and lived.

359
00:21:19,121 --> 00:21:20,641
-(GUNSHOT)
-(BILL GASPS)

360
00:21:24,601 --> 00:21:26,201
Go and see if he's all right.
Both of you.

361
00:21:26,401 --> 00:21:27,801
I think we know he isn't.

362
00:21:29,721 --> 00:21:32,001
We know nothing of the kind.
He might need help.

363
00:21:32,841 --> 00:21:35,481
Might have useful information.
He's about 50 feet that way.

364
00:21:35,561 --> 00:21:37,921
-Are you trying to get rid of us?
-Why?

365
00:21:38,001 --> 00:21:40,121
Because you're sending us into the dark
after a man with a gun.

366
00:21:40,201 --> 00:21:42,241
-Ah, well, I thought of that.
-Thank you.

367
00:21:42,321 --> 00:21:44,201
Nardole, make sure you walk
in front of Bill.

368
00:21:44,281 --> 00:21:45,481
Oh, great.

369
00:21:45,641 --> 00:21:48,401
Are you gonna read this?
Is that why you're sending us off?

370
00:21:49,481 --> 00:21:52,041
-I won't read this without you.
-Really, he won't.

371
00:21:54,281 --> 00:21:56,001
-Promise?
-Trust me.

372
00:21:56,161 --> 00:21:57,481
We'll shout if we need you.

373
00:21:58,561 --> 00:21:59,721
DOCTOR: Me too.

374
00:22:00,441 --> 00:22:02,441
BILL: Does it give you the fear
when he says, "Trust me"?

375
00:22:02,641 --> 00:22:04,681
NARDOLE: If I worked here,
I'd cross meself.

376
00:22:14,761 --> 00:22:17,961
NARDOLE: Bill, stay close by me.
There's a man with a gun.

377
00:22:22,681 --> 00:22:23,921
Uh-uh-uh.

378
00:22:25,201 --> 00:22:27,081
Yeah, you don't
actually have to do that.

379
00:22:27,361 --> 00:22:29,161
In fact, don't you dare do that.

380
00:22:29,481 --> 00:22:30,681
Uh-uh-uh, Bill.

381
00:22:31,281 --> 00:22:33,481
You're to walk behind me now,
like the Doctor said.

382
00:22:34,081 --> 00:22:36,521
(SCOFFS) Yeah. Totally not happening.

383
00:22:38,561 --> 00:22:40,441
Okay, Bill. Miss Potts.

384
00:22:41,041 --> 00:22:43,401
I'm the only person you've ever met
or will ever meet

385
00:22:43,481 --> 00:22:46,321
who is officially licensed
to kick the Doctor's arse.

386
00:22:46,401 --> 00:22:48,601
I will happily do the same to you
in the event

387
00:22:48,681 --> 00:22:51,881
that you do not align yourself
with any instructions I have issued,

388
00:22:51,961 --> 00:22:54,161
which I personally judge to be
in the best interest

389
00:22:54,241 --> 00:22:56,321
of your safety and survival.

390
00:22:57,601 --> 00:22:58,721
Okay, Bill?

391
00:22:59,001 --> 00:23:00,801
-Okay.
-Good-o!

392
00:23:02,601 --> 00:23:03,601
Nardole?

393
00:23:04,321 --> 00:23:05,841
Are you secretly a badass?

394
00:23:05,921 --> 00:23:07,801
Nothing secret about it, baby doll.

395
00:23:07,881 --> 00:23:08,921
(YELPS)

396
00:23:09,241 --> 00:23:10,921
(GASPS)

397
00:23:15,441 --> 00:23:17,241
(SIGHS) Well,
that answers that question.

398
00:23:23,881 --> 00:23:26,441
BILL: It's an opening
like we saw before.

399
00:23:26,521 --> 00:23:28,161
NARDOLE: Yeah, like a portal.

400
00:23:32,801 --> 00:23:34,641
-You're right.
-About what?

401
00:23:35,881 --> 00:23:37,881
It would be stupid to go and look.

402
00:24:03,721 --> 00:24:05,441
(TRILLS)

403
00:24:15,081 --> 00:24:17,321
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

404
00:24:17,401 --> 00:24:18,561
Cardinal Angelo.

405
00:24:18,921 --> 00:24:20,521
I could do with your help here.

406
00:24:21,761 --> 00:24:24,241
I'm not absolutely sure
how this is going to work.

407
00:24:24,721 --> 00:24:27,561
Either it's going to temporarily
fix my eyesight

408
00:24:27,641 --> 00:24:29,841
or it's going to burn out my brain.

409
00:24:32,481 --> 00:24:35,401
Just, uh, give me a moment.

410
00:24:42,961 --> 00:24:44,921
-(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)
-(GASPING)

411
00:24:46,361 --> 00:24:47,481
(GROANS)

412
00:24:52,201 --> 00:24:53,561
MISSY: I am your friend.

413
00:24:55,441 --> 00:24:56,641
Makes no difference.

414
00:24:56,841 --> 00:24:58,081
MISSY: I know it doesn't.

415
00:24:58,921 --> 00:25:00,481
I know I'm going to die.

416
00:25:00,881 --> 00:25:02,801
I have to say it. The truth.

417
00:25:04,641 --> 00:25:05,761
Without hope.

418
00:25:07,481 --> 00:25:08,841
Without witness.

419
00:25:09,241 --> 00:25:10,961
Without reward.

420
00:25:12,681 --> 00:25:15,481
(VOICE FALTERS) I am your friend.

421
00:25:17,761 --> 00:25:19,121
(GASPS)

422
00:25:20,561 --> 00:25:21,681
(EXHALES)

423
00:25:27,681 --> 00:25:30,681
On my oath as a Time Lord
of the Prydonian Chapter,

424
00:25:31,881 --> 00:25:33,601
I will guard this body

425
00:25:35,561 --> 00:25:36,961
for a thousand years.

426
00:25:45,801 --> 00:25:47,801
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

427
00:25:58,641 --> 00:26:00,121
-Hello.
-Hello.

428
00:26:00,681 --> 00:26:01,681
Who are you?

429
00:26:01,921 --> 00:26:03,921
Do you have clearance for floor three?

430
00:26:04,121 --> 00:26:05,361
Floor three of what?

431
00:26:05,761 --> 00:26:06,761
Of what?

432
00:26:07,161 --> 00:26:08,161
Of what?

433
00:26:09,561 --> 00:26:10,881
The Pentagon.

434
00:26:15,601 --> 00:26:16,601
(MUMBLES INDISTINCTLY)

435
00:26:24,281 --> 00:26:25,601
So, the Pentagon is through there.

436
00:26:25,841 --> 00:26:26,841
Yeah.

437
00:26:27,121 --> 00:26:31,881
(STUTTERING) And the Vatican
is through there.

438
00:26:32,361 --> 00:26:34,921
Huh. I wonder what's through here.

439
00:26:35,561 --> 00:26:36,641
What is this?

440
00:26:36,801 --> 00:26:39,241
-How is this possible?
-NARDOLE: Alien technology.

441
00:26:39,641 --> 00:26:41,121
Let's see what else they got.

442
00:26:41,561 --> 00:26:44,561
Ooh. Bill, come and take a look at this.

443
00:26:46,601 --> 00:26:48,521
(PANTING)

444
00:26:54,041 --> 00:26:55,761
Oh, hello.

445
00:26:56,321 --> 00:26:57,601
Are... Are you coming?

446
00:26:58,521 --> 00:26:59,521
Coming where?

447
00:26:59,841 --> 00:27:01,881
Uh, we are all in the cafeteria.

448
00:27:02,001 --> 00:27:03,241
You mustn't miss it.

449
00:27:04,001 --> 00:27:05,041
Why?

450
00:27:06,401 --> 00:27:08,441
We're all going together when we go.

451
00:27:10,441 --> 00:27:12,921
(LAUGHING) Come on!

452
00:27:17,241 --> 00:27:18,561
(GASPING)

453
00:27:21,201 --> 00:27:23,281
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

454
00:27:30,321 --> 00:27:32,441
(GROANING)

455
00:27:33,001 --> 00:27:35,681
Cardinal. It worked! I can see.

456
00:27:37,201 --> 00:27:38,881
Not well enough. Not yet.

457
00:27:40,561 --> 00:27:41,561
(GROANS)

458
00:27:42,361 --> 00:27:43,561
(BREATHING HEAVILY)
Think about the universes.

459
00:27:43,641 --> 00:27:45,921
Whatever you need,
you can always borrow.

460
00:27:46,681 --> 00:27:48,481
As long as you pay it back.

461
00:27:49,121 --> 00:27:52,001
I just borrowed from my future.

462
00:27:52,961 --> 00:27:55,881
I get a few minutes of proper eyesight

463
00:27:55,961 --> 00:27:58,121
but I lose something.

464
00:27:58,521 --> 00:28:00,721
Maybe all my future regenerations
will be blind.

465
00:28:01,081 --> 00:28:04,041
Maybe I won't regenerate ever again.

466
00:28:04,121 --> 00:28:06,281
Maybe I'll drop dead in 20 minutes,

467
00:28:07,601 --> 00:28:10,601
but I will be able to read this.

468
00:28:11,801 --> 00:28:15,201
Now, I have no idea
how that is going to affect me.

469
00:28:15,281 --> 00:28:17,801
So, I'd be a bit stupid

470
00:28:17,961 --> 00:28:20,161
to reject the precautions provided.

471
00:28:20,241 --> 00:28:22,121
Could you help me, please?

472
00:28:22,201 --> 00:28:23,201
Could you help me?

473
00:28:23,921 --> 00:28:25,801
(BUCKLES CLICKING)

474
00:28:28,801 --> 00:28:31,841
Now, I've read a lot of books that
this chair would be quite useful for.

475
00:28:33,241 --> 00:28:37,041
Moby Dick. Honestly, shut up
and get to the whale.

476
00:28:42,041 --> 00:28:44,001
Have you invited friends and family?

477
00:28:48,321 --> 00:28:50,201
-(GASPS)
-(BREATHES HOARSELY)

478
00:28:50,761 --> 00:28:52,961
Oh, it's the old, old story.

479
00:28:53,881 --> 00:28:55,441
They never look so good in the morning.

480
00:28:58,401 --> 00:29:00,761
Goodbye to the truth.
I came a long way to read that book.

481
00:29:00,841 --> 00:29:02,561
Two thousand years at the last count.

482
00:29:05,201 --> 00:29:06,281
If you don't want me to read it,

483
00:29:06,361 --> 00:29:07,441
you could've stopped me
any time you wanted.

484
00:29:07,521 --> 00:29:09,761
Why the play acting? This is not a game.

485
00:29:09,841 --> 00:29:12,121
This is a game.

486
00:29:12,201 --> 00:29:13,521
DOCTOR: Good, because I win!

487
00:29:13,601 --> 00:29:14,681
(GRUNTS)

488
00:29:15,201 --> 00:29:17,321
MONK: Doctor!

489
00:29:17,681 --> 00:29:19,681
-Doctor!
-(DOCTOR GRUNTING)

490
00:29:26,481 --> 00:29:28,521
(BREATHING HOARSELY)

491
00:29:29,081 --> 00:29:32,041
Doctor, we have the Veritas.

492
00:29:38,001 --> 00:29:40,001
(PANTING)

493
00:29:45,721 --> 00:29:47,121
Come, come, come, come.

494
00:29:47,961 --> 00:29:49,001
BILL: CERN.

495
00:29:49,081 --> 00:29:50,881
NARDOLE: Where what's-his-name
sent the Veritas.

496
00:29:51,001 --> 00:29:52,201
Ladies and gentlemen.

497
00:29:52,561 --> 00:29:53,961
(GLASS CLINKING)

498
00:29:54,041 --> 00:29:55,601
Your attention, please!

499
00:29:59,441 --> 00:30:01,201
I've been around everywhere

500
00:30:01,321 --> 00:30:02,921
and I've checked everything.

501
00:30:03,001 --> 00:30:04,201
It's all ready to go.

502
00:30:05,441 --> 00:30:06,601
Five minutes.

503
00:30:08,321 --> 00:30:10,361
Last orders, please.

504
00:30:10,761 --> 00:30:11,961
(CRYING)

505
00:30:20,681 --> 00:30:21,761
WOMAN: Cheers.

506
00:30:26,681 --> 00:30:28,721
(WHISPERING) Look under the tables.

507
00:30:33,281 --> 00:30:35,161
(TICKING)

508
00:30:40,481 --> 00:30:42,241
Oh, my God.

509
00:31:14,361 --> 00:31:15,841
(KEYS CLACKING)

510
00:31:18,921 --> 00:31:20,401
(SIGHS) Oh, no.

511
00:31:21,041 --> 00:31:22,201
(GRUNTS) Oh, no!

512
00:31:24,321 --> 00:31:26,121
No! Not yet!

513
00:31:26,321 --> 00:31:27,401
No!

514
00:31:27,721 --> 00:31:29,281
No, no, no, no!

515
00:31:45,521 --> 00:31:46,641
(HOARSE GROWLING)

516
00:31:49,641 --> 00:31:50,961
(HOARSE GROWLING)

517
00:31:53,561 --> 00:31:54,881
(HOARSE GROWLING)

518
00:31:55,041 --> 00:31:56,521
(PANTING)

519
00:31:56,761 --> 00:31:57,801
(GASPS)

520
00:31:59,281 --> 00:32:00,361
(GROANS)

521
00:32:12,521 --> 00:32:13,881
In vino veritas.

522
00:32:14,001 --> 00:32:15,721
Why are you doing this?

523
00:32:15,801 --> 00:32:17,041
You've got explosives.

524
00:32:17,121 --> 00:32:18,841
We're saving the world.

525
00:32:18,921 --> 00:32:20,761
You know, we should go.

526
00:32:20,841 --> 00:32:22,721
We should probably even run.

527
00:32:22,801 --> 00:32:25,041
How is blowing yourselves up
saving the world?

528
00:32:25,441 --> 00:32:28,121
Because this isn't the world.

529
00:32:28,721 --> 00:32:31,401
-This isn't what?
-Bill, time. Tiny bit running out.

530
00:32:32,481 --> 00:32:33,601
You haven't read it?

531
00:32:34,801 --> 00:32:36,481
You haven't read the Veritas?

532
00:32:36,561 --> 00:32:39,241
Sorry, I'd love to but must dash.

533
00:32:40,161 --> 00:32:41,561
Choose a number.

534
00:32:42,801 --> 00:32:44,841
Any number. Both of you.

535
00:32:45,201 --> 00:32:46,241
Now.

536
00:32:47,361 --> 00:32:50,201
And say it when I tap this table.

537
00:32:53,561 --> 00:32:55,081
(BANGS TABLE)

538
00:32:55,641 --> 00:32:56,921
BOTH: 36.

539
00:32:59,801 --> 00:33:01,601
Try again. Keep going.

540
00:33:02,801 --> 00:33:03,801
(BANGS TABLE)

541
00:33:03,881 --> 00:33:04,881
BOTH: 17.

542
00:33:04,961 --> 00:33:06,121
-Huh?
-MAN: Again.

543
00:33:06,201 --> 00:33:08,761
Don't stop. Every time I tap the table.

544
00:33:09,001 --> 00:33:10,041
(BANGS TABLE)

545
00:33:10,121 --> 00:33:11,161
BOTH: 9.

546
00:33:11,241 --> 00:33:12,641
BOTH: 48.

547
00:33:12,721 --> 00:33:14,401
BOTH: 1035.

548
00:33:14,481 --> 00:33:15,801
BOTH: A million.

549
00:33:15,881 --> 00:33:17,601
BOTH: Seven billion and seven.

550
00:33:17,681 --> 00:33:18,721
(LAUGHS)

551
00:33:18,961 --> 00:33:20,041
67.

552
00:33:20,161 --> 00:33:22,041
-(BANGS TABLE)
-BOTH: 905.

553
00:33:22,761 --> 00:33:24,881
ALL: 20,460.

554
00:33:25,001 --> 00:33:26,761
-(BANGS TABLE)
-ALL: Twelve.

555
00:33:26,841 --> 00:33:28,521
-(BANGS TABLE)
-ALL: Four.

556
00:33:28,601 --> 00:33:30,681
-(BANGS TABLE)
-ALL: 87.

557
00:33:30,761 --> 00:33:32,121
-(BANGS TABLE)
-ALL: 702.

558
00:33:32,201 --> 00:33:34,161
What is this? How are you doing that?

559
00:33:34,241 --> 00:33:35,601
MAN: It's a test.

560
00:33:36,041 --> 00:33:37,521
It's a shadow test.

561
00:33:38,921 --> 00:33:41,441
Oh. I'm really very sorry.

562
00:33:41,521 --> 00:33:42,841
(CHUCKLES)

563
00:33:50,001 --> 00:33:51,721
ALL: Ten, nine,

564
00:33:51,801 --> 00:33:54,881
eight, seven, six,

565
00:33:54,961 --> 00:34:00,281
five, four, three, two, one!

566
00:34:02,561 --> 00:34:04,801
Okay, what was that about?

567
00:34:04,881 --> 00:34:06,041
Those numbers, how did they do that?

568
00:34:06,121 --> 00:34:07,441
Ooh.

569
00:34:07,521 --> 00:34:08,881
Ooh.

570
00:34:08,961 --> 00:34:10,081
Oh!

571
00:34:10,161 --> 00:34:11,961
-You okay?
-No.

572
00:34:13,281 --> 00:34:14,401
Yes.

573
00:34:14,881 --> 00:34:15,921
No!

574
00:34:16,121 --> 00:34:18,601
-(WHIMPERS)
-BILL: Someone's been through here.

575
00:34:21,401 --> 00:34:22,801
Could be the Doctor.

576
00:34:24,601 --> 00:34:26,281
Those things.

577
00:34:26,841 --> 00:34:28,321
What do they look like?

578
00:34:28,401 --> 00:34:29,921
-Projectors.
-Exactly.

579
00:34:30,001 --> 00:34:31,881
-Exactly.
-Yeah, they're projecting the portals.

580
00:34:31,961 --> 00:34:33,161
No, they're not.

581
00:34:33,241 --> 00:34:34,361
They're projecting everything.

582
00:34:34,441 --> 00:34:36,921
Those worlds, they're all projected.

583
00:34:37,041 --> 00:34:39,641
The Pentagon, the Vatican, CERN...

584
00:34:39,721 --> 00:34:41,961
-They're not real?
-No, no! They're holograms.

585
00:34:42,041 --> 00:34:45,721
They're holographic simulations
and the people in them, too.

586
00:34:45,801 --> 00:34:47,241
Sorry, what?

587
00:34:47,321 --> 00:34:48,841
You know, like the holodeck on Star Trek

588
00:34:48,921 --> 00:34:51,001
or a really posh VR without a headset.

589
00:34:51,081 --> 00:34:54,601
Through there, those places,
that's basically Grand Theft Auto.

590
00:34:55,121 --> 00:34:56,241
It can't be.

591
00:34:56,321 --> 00:34:59,201
It is! Look at the tech!
It definitely is!

592
00:35:00,321 --> 00:35:02,081
What? Sorry,
you're not making any sense.

593
00:35:02,161 --> 00:35:03,961
When did we end up in a computer game?

594
00:35:04,041 --> 00:35:05,561
When did that start?

595
00:35:05,641 --> 00:35:08,841
I... I don't know. Maybe when we arrived
at the Vatican?

596
00:35:08,921 --> 00:35:10,961
But I programmed the TARDIS myself.

597
00:35:11,041 --> 00:35:12,761
We were on target,
we went to the Vatican,

598
00:35:12,841 --> 00:35:14,281
the real one, I'm sure of it.

599
00:35:15,761 --> 00:35:16,801
Oh.

600
00:35:17,241 --> 00:35:18,241
Oh?

601
00:35:18,601 --> 00:35:20,561
Those machines, they...

602
00:35:21,481 --> 00:35:23,081
...project the simulations.

603
00:35:23,161 --> 00:35:24,521
Yeah?

604
00:35:24,881 --> 00:35:27,241
And I'm just wondering...

605
00:35:29,161 --> 00:35:31,081
What happens if

606
00:35:31,761 --> 00:35:34,961
we move outside
the light of the projector.

607
00:35:36,161 --> 00:35:37,881
Don't let me be right.

608
00:35:37,961 --> 00:35:40,681
Please don't let me be right.

609
00:35:45,961 --> 00:35:47,281
(EXCLAIMS)

610
00:35:47,721 --> 00:35:49,161
I'm part of it!

611
00:35:49,281 --> 00:35:51,001
I'm part of the simulation!

612
00:35:51,281 --> 00:35:53,521
Bill, I'm not real!

613
00:35:54,161 --> 00:35:55,881
(SCREAMS) Bill!

614
00:35:56,441 --> 00:35:57,921
Nardole!

615
00:36:03,881 --> 00:36:05,041
(GASPS SOFTLY)

616
00:36:15,041 --> 00:36:16,081
Doctor.

617
00:36:20,881 --> 00:36:21,961
Doctor?

618
00:36:36,321 --> 00:36:37,641
(DOOR CREAKING)

619
00:36:54,841 --> 00:36:56,001
-Bill, is that you?
-(GASPS)

620
00:36:58,201 --> 00:36:59,601
Hello, Doctor.

621
00:37:02,081 --> 00:37:03,481
Is that the president?

622
00:37:04,921 --> 00:37:06,081
It was.

623
00:37:13,441 --> 00:37:15,161
BILL: I take it he read the Ver/tas.

624
00:37:16,281 --> 00:37:17,441
So did 1.

625
00:37:20,201 --> 00:37:21,401
Well...

626
00:37:22,281 --> 00:37:23,601
I listened to it.

627
00:37:23,841 --> 00:37:27,201
There's this thing on here that reads
aloud to you. It's very useful.

628
00:37:27,281 --> 00:37:28,761
Who needs Nardole?

629
00:37:31,481 --> 00:37:32,761
Where is Nardole?

630
00:37:37,521 --> 00:37:40,521
I need to know what's real
and what isn't real.

631
00:37:40,601 --> 00:37:42,721
-Don't we all?
-Don't play games.

632
00:37:43,321 --> 00:37:44,681
Tell me.

633
00:37:51,721 --> 00:37:52,881
Uh...

634
00:37:56,001 --> 00:37:57,681
The Veritastells

635
00:37:58,841 --> 00:38:02,201
of an evil demon
who wants to conquer the world.

636
00:38:03,481 --> 00:38:04,961
But to do it,

637
00:38:05,521 --> 00:38:07,401
he needs to learn about it first.

638
00:38:07,561 --> 00:38:09,641
So he creates a shadow world.

639
00:38:10,681 --> 00:38:13,721
A world for him to practise conquering.

640
00:38:14,641 --> 00:38:16,841
Full of shadow people
who think they're real.

641
00:38:17,401 --> 00:38:19,641
There was a... A thing.

642
00:38:19,721 --> 00:38:20,921
The shadow test?

643
00:38:21,281 --> 00:38:23,361
If you're in doubt
whether you're real or not,

644
00:38:23,441 --> 00:38:26,841
the Veritas invites you to write down
as many numbers as you like.

645
00:38:26,921 --> 00:38:29,441
Of any size, any order.

646
00:38:30,201 --> 00:38:31,601
And then turn the page.

647
00:38:31,681 --> 00:38:34,601
All the same numbers in the same order.

648
00:38:35,121 --> 00:38:36,521
Yes.

649
00:38:41,441 --> 00:38:43,761
Let's bring the story up to date, Bill.

650
00:38:44,121 --> 00:38:46,521
Imagine an alien life form

651
00:38:46,601 --> 00:38:48,641
of immense power

652
00:38:49,601 --> 00:38:51,001
and sophistication,

653
00:38:51,201 --> 00:38:53,481
and it wants to conquer the Earth.

654
00:38:53,881 --> 00:38:56,041
So it runs a simulation.

655
00:38:56,401 --> 00:38:59,041
A holographic simulation

656
00:38:59,441 --> 00:39:04,561
of all of Earth's history
and every person alive on the surface,

657
00:39:04,641 --> 00:39:05,961
a practice Earth,

658
00:39:06,041 --> 00:39:10,361
to assess the abilities
of the resident population.

659
00:39:10,881 --> 00:39:13,881
Especially the ones
smart enough to realise

660
00:39:13,961 --> 00:39:16,161
that they are just simulants

661
00:39:16,241 --> 00:39:19,481
inside a great big computer game.

662
00:39:20,561 --> 00:39:23,201
But... But this is... This... This...

663
00:39:23,281 --> 00:39:26,161
This... This is real. I... I feel it.

664
00:39:29,081 --> 00:39:31,601
Computers aren't good
with random numbers.

665
00:39:32,681 --> 00:39:34,961
If you ask a computer-simulated person

666
00:39:35,041 --> 00:39:37,601
to generate a random string of numbers,

667
00:39:37,681 --> 00:39:40,841
it won't truly be random.

668
00:39:42,761 --> 00:39:45,401
If all the simulated people

669
00:39:45,481 --> 00:39:48,281
are part of the same computer program,

670
00:39:48,361 --> 00:39:52,041
then they'll all generate
the same string.

671
00:39:52,561 --> 00:39:55,441
The exact same numbers.

672
00:39:55,521 --> 00:39:57,961
The... The numbers...

673
00:40:00,561 --> 00:40:02,841
I said them, too.

674
00:40:02,921 --> 00:40:04,361
I know.

675
00:40:06,121 --> 00:40:07,481
So did 1.

676
00:40:08,761 --> 00:40:09,961
The trouble is,

677
00:40:10,161 --> 00:40:13,361
when simulants develop enough
independent intelligence

678
00:40:13,441 --> 00:40:15,441
to realise what they are,

679
00:40:15,521 --> 00:40:17,321
there's a risk they'll rebel.

680
00:40:17,801 --> 00:40:19,321
Those deaths...

681
00:40:19,921 --> 00:40:21,641
They weren't suicide.

682
00:40:21,761 --> 00:40:23,401
Those were people...

683
00:40:24,361 --> 00:40:25,481
(SIGHS)

684
00:40:26,601 --> 00:40:27,721
...escaping.

685
00:40:28,361 --> 00:40:31,921
It's like, um, Super Mario.

686
00:40:33,001 --> 00:40:35,001
Figuring out what's going on.

687
00:40:36,521 --> 00:40:38,441
Deleting himself from the game

688
00:40:39,521 --> 00:40:41,001
because he's sick of dying.

689
00:40:44,201 --> 00:40:46,681
No, I'm real. I feel real.

690
00:40:46,761 --> 00:40:48,161
Those pretend people

691
00:40:48,241 --> 00:40:50,961
you shoot at in computer games...

692
00:40:53,241 --> 00:40:55,241
-Now you know.
-Know what?

693
00:40:55,321 --> 00:40:56,521
They think they're real.

694
00:40:56,601 --> 00:40:57,961
They feel it.

695
00:40:59,281 --> 00:41:00,721
We feel it.

696
00:41:05,041 --> 00:41:06,801
(GASPING)

697
00:41:07,761 --> 00:41:09,081
(VOICE BREAKING) Help me.

698
00:41:10,321 --> 00:41:11,361
Help me.

699
00:41:11,441 --> 00:41:13,321
Bill, what's happening to you?

700
00:41:13,921 --> 00:41:15,401
Save me.

701
00:41:22,321 --> 00:41:23,561
DOCTOR: Bill, are you there?

702
00:41:23,641 --> 00:41:25,401
She was not real.

703
00:41:25,481 --> 00:41:27,321
You are not real.

704
00:41:27,401 --> 00:41:29,401
No, I'm not. I'm a shadow.

705
00:41:29,561 --> 00:41:32,681
A puppet doctor for you
to practise killing.

706
00:41:32,921 --> 00:41:36,081
We have killed you many times.

707
00:41:36,161 --> 00:41:38,201
Then what are you waiting for?
Why don't you kill me now?

708
00:41:38,281 --> 00:41:40,281
You suffer.

709
00:41:40,641 --> 00:41:43,401
Pain is information.

710
00:41:43,961 --> 00:41:46,801
Information will be gathered.

711
00:41:49,881 --> 00:41:51,121
Turn me off.

712
00:41:51,601 --> 00:41:52,761
Turn me off.

713
00:41:53,841 --> 00:41:54,921
I have nothing.

714
00:41:55,121 --> 00:41:56,281
Not even hope.

715
00:41:56,921 --> 00:41:58,001
Without hope.

716
00:42:00,121 --> 00:42:01,201
Without witness.

717
00:42:02,641 --> 00:42:04,161
Without reward.

718
00:42:12,681 --> 00:42:14,001
Funny.

719
00:42:16,881 --> 00:42:18,521
I don't believe much.

720
00:42:21,841 --> 00:42:23,761
I'm not sure I believe anything.

721
00:42:26,721 --> 00:42:28,441
But right now...

722
00:42:30,121 --> 00:42:32,081
...belief is all I am.

723
00:42:36,081 --> 00:42:40,321
Virtue is only virtue in extremis.

724
00:42:41,761 --> 00:42:45,481
I take it that your intention
is to invade the Earth.

725
00:42:45,881 --> 00:42:48,841
The simulations have been run.

726
00:42:48,921 --> 00:42:50,921
The Earth will be ours.

727
00:42:51,001 --> 00:42:54,361
Well, consider this a warning.

728
00:42:54,921 --> 00:42:56,201
On the eve of war,

729
00:42:56,281 --> 00:42:58,361
I am the Doctor.

730
00:43:00,121 --> 00:43:01,361
I._..

731
00:43:01,801 --> 00:43:04,041
...am what stands between you and them!

732
00:43:04,441 --> 00:43:06,321
You are not the Doctor.

733
00:43:06,401 --> 00:43:07,641
You are not real.

734
00:43:07,761 --> 00:43:10,641
You don't have to be real
to be the Doctor.

735
00:43:11,721 --> 00:43:13,481
As long as you never give up.

736
00:43:16,241 --> 00:43:20,801
Long as you always trick
the bad guys into their own traps.

737
00:43:22,161 --> 00:43:23,961
And here's the trap you fell into.

738
00:43:24,041 --> 00:43:27,001
Your simulation is far too good.

739
00:43:31,161 --> 00:43:32,601
See these?

740
00:43:32,961 --> 00:43:34,481
They're set to record.

741
00:43:34,561 --> 00:43:36,001
I'm blind, you see.

742
00:43:36,401 --> 00:43:39,361
So I'm psychically wired into these.

743
00:43:39,441 --> 00:43:41,761
So my memory print
of the last few hours

744
00:43:41,841 --> 00:43:44,361
will still be intact on here.

745
00:43:44,441 --> 00:43:46,761
Information about you.

746
00:43:46,841 --> 00:43:50,841
You are not real.
There is nothing you can do.

747
00:43:53,881 --> 00:43:56,281
There's always one thing
you can do from inside a computer,

748
00:43:56,361 --> 00:43:59,441
even if you're a jumped up
little sub-routine, you can do it.

749
00:43:59,521 --> 00:44:00,561
You can always...

750
00:44:01,961 --> 00:44:03,081
...e-mail.

751
00:44:07,161 --> 00:44:09,081
What are you doing?

752
00:44:09,441 --> 00:44:12,401
I'm doing what everybody does
when the world is in danger.

753
00:44:12,481 --> 00:44:13,801
I'm calling the Doctor.

754
00:44:13,881 --> 00:44:15,241
Pressing send.

755
00:44:28,161 --> 00:44:29,561
(GLASSES CHIME)

756
00:44:43,201 --> 00:44:45,241
(MOBILE PHONE RINGING)

757
00:44:52,681 --> 00:44:55,641
I'm doing it, I'm doing it.
The essay, I'm doing it.

758
00:44:55,721 --> 00:44:57,361
-Are you on a date?
-No.

759
00:44:57,441 --> 00:45:00,001
-Are you sure?
-I think I'd kind of notice.

760
00:45:00,081 --> 00:45:01,641
What about Penny?
Do you know a girl called Penny?

761
00:45:01,721 --> 00:45:03,641
-Well, yeah.
-What's she like?

762
00:45:03,721 --> 00:45:04,801
Out of my league.

763
00:45:04,881 --> 00:45:06,401
-No.
-Sorry, what?

764
00:45:06,481 --> 00:45:08,121
-No?
-No.

765
00:45:08,201 --> 00:45:09,281
What does that mean, "no"?

766
00:45:09,361 --> 00:45:11,161
It means I'm a scary
handsome genius from space

767
00:45:11,241 --> 00:45:13,241
and I'm telling you, no,
she's not out of your league.

768
00:45:13,321 --> 00:45:15,441
Okay, well,
maybe I'll call her tomorrow.

769
00:45:15,521 --> 00:45:17,241
-Call her tonight.
-Tonight?

770
00:45:17,321 --> 00:45:18,681
Something's coming, Bill.

771
00:45:18,761 --> 00:45:20,361
Something very big.

772
00:45:20,441 --> 00:45:23,201
And something possibly very, very bad.

773
00:45:23,281 --> 00:45:26,081
And I have the feeling
that we're gonna be fairly busy.

774
00:45:26,361 --> 00:45:28,081
Call her tonight.

775
00:45:43,881 --> 00:45:45,001
Listen.

776
00:45:45,081 --> 00:45:46,961
If it comes down to it,

777
00:45:47,041 --> 00:45:49,641
if you're all I've got left,
then I need your help.

778
00:45:49,721 --> 00:45:52,161
You said you were my friend.

779
00:45:55,521 --> 00:45:57,281
Oi! Get off!

780
00:45:58,841 --> 00:46:00,561
I've just been executed.

781
00:46:00,641 --> 00:46:02,241
Show a little respect.

782
00:46:02,361 --> 00:46:04,561
She's... She's alive.

783
00:46:04,641 --> 00:46:06,561
I was just a bit sleepy, all right?

784
00:46:06,641 --> 00:46:09,281
Let's not split hairs. Shut up.

785
00:46:12,121 --> 00:46:13,321
Night-night.

786
00:46:13,441 --> 00:46:15,241
DOCTOR: Of course she's not dead.

787
00:46:15,321 --> 00:46:18,721
She's a friend of mine. I may have
fiddled with your wiring a little bit.

788
00:46:18,801 --> 00:46:20,081
You swore an oath.

789
00:46:20,161 --> 00:46:22,841
I swore an oath I'd look after
her body for a thousand years.

790
00:46:22,921 --> 00:46:24,121
Nobody mentioned dead.

791
00:46:24,201 --> 00:46:25,881
You cannot do this.

792
00:46:25,961 --> 00:46:27,921
You will not leave this planet alive.

793
00:46:28,001 --> 00:46:29,401
Do me a favour,

794
00:46:29,481 --> 00:46:31,761
the fatality index,
look up "The Doctor”.

795
00:46:31,841 --> 00:46:35,561
You have an entry
just like any other sentient being.

796
00:46:35,641 --> 00:46:37,081
Under "cause of death".

797
00:46:37,161 --> 00:46:39,201
(BEEPING)

798
00:46:41,041 --> 00:46:42,641
(DEVICE TICKING)

799
00:46:42,721 --> 00:46:44,721
You do seem to have, uh,

800
00:46:45,041 --> 00:46:47,001
an impressive record

801
00:46:47,201 --> 00:46:49,641
of fatalities credited to you.
(CHUCKLES)

802
00:46:50,041 --> 00:46:52,201
(DEVICE TICKING RAPIDLY)

803
00:46:53,481 --> 00:46:55,161
A truly remarkable record.

804
00:46:57,281 --> 00:46:58,361
Where are you going?

805
00:46:58,441 --> 00:46:59,761
He's unarmed.

806
00:47:00,201 --> 00:47:02,281
-You are unarmed.
-Always.

807
00:47:02,361 --> 00:47:04,201
(DEVICE TICKING RAPIDLY)

808
00:47:06,641 --> 00:47:07,801
You stand alone?

809
00:47:07,881 --> 00:47:08,921
Often.

810
00:47:09,001 --> 00:47:10,721
You're the one who should be afraid.

811
00:47:10,801 --> 00:47:11,881
Never.

812
00:47:12,241 --> 00:47:13,641
Have a nice day then.

813
00:47:17,001 --> 00:47:19,881
Nardole, help me move Missy
to the vault.

814
00:47:24,601 --> 00:47:26,281
DOCTOR: Something's coming, Missy,

815
00:47:26,401 --> 00:47:27,921
and I'm blind.

816
00:47:28,161 --> 00:47:30,001
How can I save them

817
00:47:30,081 --> 00:47:31,921
when I'm lost in the dark?

818
00:47:42,321 --> 00:47:44,361
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

819
00:48:12,441 --> 00:48:13,801
Tell me what you see.

820
00:48:13,881 --> 00:48:15,321
BILL: It's a 5,000-year-old pyramid.

821
00:48:15,441 --> 00:48:18,001
One little problem,
it wasn't there yesterday.

822
00:48:18,081 --> 00:48:20,241
DOCTOR: Those creatures in
that pyramid, they have studied you.

823
00:48:20,321 --> 00:48:23,801
And they have chosen this exact moment
and this exact place.

824
00:48:24,961 --> 00:48:26,201
What's wrong with the Doctor?

825
00:48:26,321 --> 00:48:29,001
DOCTOR: I lied. I've been blind
since Chasm Forge.

826
00:48:29,921 --> 00:48:31,241
Co-ordinate your attacks.

827
00:48:31,321 --> 00:48:32,761
It did not come here in peace.

828
00:48:32,841 --> 00:48:35,681
MONK: We will take this planet
and its people.

829
00:48:35,801 --> 00:48:40,641
Life on Earth will cease
by humanity's own hand.

